OK, that does sound like there’s a short.  I’d check the screws to be sure:

They are the ones that came with the CANcoders;

They are screwed all the way down;

The edges of the Phillips (plus-shaped) recess haven’t been chewed up, leaving sharp protrusions.

If the screws check out, double check the plastic to be sure there isn’t something different with the ones that short.  The next step I’d consider is either putting a piece of electrical tape over the screw heads and running with that, or contacting CTRE .
